	
Difference between Functional and Non Functional Testing
Functional Testing
Verify each function/feature of software		
Manual Testing	
Based on customer requirement	
Describe what the product does	
Example : Log in functionally


Non Functional Testing
Verify non functional aspects like performance, Usability, reliability
Automation testing, Hard to done manually.
Based on customers Expectation.
Describe how the product does.
Example : How long it takes to login
